.Problems with lower-for-lower scheme
[CAUTION]
====

* 2{C}{ndash}2{D}{semicolon}3M{ndash}4{D} seems natural because opener
  has shown primary {D}.  So it should be natural.
* We don't use lower-for-lower anywhere else => inconsistent with our system
* We do use new-suit agrees secondary-suit in other situations
  => hard to remember that this one-off rare instance is different
* Responder has not yet had a chance to make a second-negative or
  show positive values.
  If M{eq}{H}, and responder fits {H}, then the auction will be at 4{D}
  leaving opener no room to make a general try below game.
  This problem does not exist when responder fits {D} because game is
  a level higher
====
